## Design: Ride-Sharing Service (Uber/Lyft): Capacity Estimation

### The Estimation Framework
1. **Start with DAU** (Daily Active Users)
2. **Calculate QPS**: DAU × actions/user/day ÷ 86,400
3. **Peak QPS**: Average × 3 (peak multiplier)
4. **Storage**: writes/day × record size × retention period
5. **Bandwidth**: QPS × response size

### Numbers to Remember
| Resource | Throughput |
|----------|----------|
| Web server | 2,000-5,000 RPS |
| Redis | 100,000 ops/sec |
| PostgreSQL | 10,000 queries/sec |
| Kafka | 100,000 msg/sec |
| SSD | 200,000 IOPS |

### Server Estimation
```
Peak QPS ÷ throughput_per_server × 1.3 (30% headroom) = servers needed
```

### Interview Tip
"Back-of-envelope calculations impress interviewers. Always round to powers of 10 for quick math. State your assumptions clearly."

